                            <comment id="13270485" author="hustlmsp" created="Tue, 8 May 2012 15:26:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;add documents about compaction.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13270876" author="fpj" created="Tue, 8 May 2012 23:03:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Sijie, I have edited it a bit, please make sure I didn&apos;t break anything in this new patch. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While reading it, I had a question: what if we set the compaction interval to zero? Do we have a check in place to make sure that it is not going to perform compaction continuously? On top of making sure the behavior is correct, it might be a good idea to update the documentation to reflect it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13271022" author="hustlmsp" created="Wed, 9 May 2012 03:29:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;@Flavio, thanks for editing the documents.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;  what if we set the compaction interval to zero? Do we have a check in place to make sure that it is not going to perform compaction continuously?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if the compaction interval is set to zero, the compaction would be disabled. there is code to check and disable it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would update the documents based your new patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13271118" author="hustlmsp" created="Wed, 9 May 2012 06:43:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;update a new patch based on Flavio&apos;s modification, which addressed Flavio&apos;s comment, changing &apos;negative value&apos; to &apos;less than or equal to zero&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13271170" author="fpj" created="Wed, 9 May 2012 08:16:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, Thanks sijie.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13271171" author="fpj" created="Wed, 9 May 2012 08:17:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1335947.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
